#Splitting the Blood Pressure Column into Systolic and Diastolic Pressures

dataset[['Systolic BP', 'Diastolic BP']] = dataset['BP(mmHg'].str.split('/', expand=True)
df=dataset.drop(['BP(mmHg','NAME'], axis=1)
#to maintain confidentiality the name axis must be dropped.

#Calculating average pressures and average sugar levels
average_systolic_pressure = df['Systolic BP'].astype(float).mean()
average_diastolic_pressure = df['Diastolic BP'].astype(float).mean()
average_RBS = df['RBS(mmol/L)'].astype(float).mean()

print("Average RBS:", average_RBS)

The condition and medication columns seems to have clustered and unorganized data in them therefore they must individually be broken into multiple columns with each column having one condition or medication

Participants with missing values for RBS and Blood rate are liekly to be children whose blood sugar level and blood rate were not taken, its absence does not necessarily affect this analysis. Null values for Conditions and Medication columns are due to the fact that not all patients have up to 7 conditions or medications. To avoid misrepresentation of data, category for data with missing age will be created so that it is olso analysed

In [254]:
#Categorising the age variable and grouping the data according ages

age_bins = [0, 10, 18, 40, 60, np.inf]
age_labels = ['0-10','11-18', '19-40', '41-60', '60+']

df['Age_Category'] = pd.cut(df['AGE'], bins=age_bins, labels=age_labels, right=False)

df['Age_Category'] = df['Age_Category'].cat.add_categories(['Unknown'])

df['Age_Category'].fillna('Unknown', inplace=True)

data= df.set_index('Age_Category').sort_values('Age_Category', ascending = True)

#concatenating the dataframes
